name: Lynx Air 737 MAXs - Final Flights at Calgary International Airport
description:
During the last weekend of February, Lynx Air wound down their operations and steadily got their fleet of nine Boeing 737 MAXs back to their base in Calgary.

After flying their last passenger flights, all nine of their planes were briefly parked at Calgary International Airport for just a few days.

On February 29th though, the nine airplanes flew again one more time, ferrying to Tucson, Arizona, for further storage.

So, as one last little tribute to Lynx Air, here's a compilation of some of their final revenue flights, as well as a few of the ferry flights, including the last ever departure from Calgary.
